{"id":220817030,"name":"Using Semantic Cues to Learn Syntax.","abstraction":"This paper presents two Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) algorithms for Bayesian inference of probabilistic con- text free grammars (PCFGs) from ter- minal strings, providing an alternative to maximum-likelihood estimation using the Inside-Outside algorithm. We illus- trate these methods by estimating a sparse grammar describing the morphology of the Bantu language Sesotho, demonstrat- ing that with suitable priors Bayesian techniques can infer linguistic structure in situations where maximum likelihood methods such as the Inside-Outside algo- rithm only produce a trivial grammar.","authors":["Mark Johnson","Thomas L. Griffiths","Sharon Goldwater"],"citedInUrls":["https://www.researchgate.net/publication/221604409_Using_Semantic_Cues_to_Learn_Syntax","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/220875091_Bayesian_Word_Alignment_for_Statistical_Machine_Translation","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/220873182_A_Bayesian_Model_for_Unsupervised_Semantic_Parsing"],"refrenceUrls":["https://www.researchgate.net/publication/202880304_Random_Number_Generation_and_Monte_Carlo_Methods","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/7701181_Ding_Y_Chan_CY_Lawrence_CE_RNA_secondary_structure_prediction_by_centroids_in_a_Boltzmann_weighted_ensemble_RNA_11_1157-1166","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/222491221_The_Estimation_of_Stochastic_Context-Free_Grammars_Using_the_Inside-Outside_Algorithm","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/221012856_Solving_the_Problem_of_Cascading_Errors_Approximate_Bayesian_Inference_for_Linguistic_Annotation_Pipelines","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/220874243_Corpus-Based_Induction_of_Syntactic_Structure_Models_of_Dependency_and_Constituency","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/220873322_Annealing_Structural_Bias_in_Multilingual_Weighted_Grammar_Induction","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/247743975_The_acquisition_of_Sesotho","https://www.